ce:section.ce:para:
Novelties in brief.

                           1.

Introduction of the Average Effective Diffusivity Tensor (AEDT);


                           2.

Novel concept of connectivity tensor for 3D anisotropic structures based on the inverse of the (diagonal) tortuosity tensor;


                           3.

New procedure of digital reconstruction of real structures for CFD purpose;


                           4.

Calculation of the defined connectivity tensor by steady-state pure-diffusion CFD simulations, which avoids time-dependent diffusivities.

where it is stated that, in the natural extension to the three-dimensional case, the effective diffusivity tensor can be expressed by the product of the unconstrained (free) diffusion coefficient D and the porosity of the structure ε – which are both scalars – with the tortuosity tensor. Therefore, to calculate the diagonal tortuosity tensor τ (
